**Definition 4.2** (Encoder Rank).: _For any \(\bm{h}\in\mathcal{E}_{V}\) let the **encoder rank** be \(\mathrm{rank}(\bm{h})\stackrel{{\text{\tiny def}}}{{=}}\dim_{ \mathbb{R}}(V_{\bm{h}})\), where \(V_{\bm{h}}\) is the subvector space generated by the image of \(\bm{h}\). When \(\mathrm{rank}(\bm{h})=\dim_{\mathbb{R}}(V)\), \(\bm{h}\) is a **full rank** encoder, else it is **rank deficient**._

**Theorem 4.1**.: _For \(\bm{h},\bm{g}\in\mathcal{E}_{V}\), we have_

\[\bm{h}\succsim_{\mathrm{Aff}}\bm{g}\Leftrightarrow\bm{h}=\psi(\bm{\pi}_{\bm{ h}}\circ\bm{g})\text{ for some }\psi\in\mathrm{Aff}(V)\] (10)

