This allows us to state our first notion of language encoder similarity: intrinsic affine homotopy.

**Definition 4.3** (Exact Intrinsic Affine Homotopy).: _We say that two encoders \(\bm{h},\bm{g}\in\mathcal{E}_{V}\) are **exactly intrinsically affinely homotopic** and write \(\bm{h}\simeq_{\mathrm{Aff}}\bm{g}\) if_

